Parliament, Thursday, 16 January 2023 – The Portfolio Committee on Forestry, Fisheries and Environment will from tomorrow visit Limpopo Province to conduct public hearings on the Climate Change Bill. The Bill seeks to ensure the effective management of inevitable climate change impacts by enhancing adaptive capacity, strengthening resilience and reducing vulnerability to climate change, with a view to building social, economic and environmental resilience and adequate national adaptation response in the context of the global climate change response. The committee invites all interested citizens and organisations to attend the public hearings and comment on the Climate Change Bill. Details of the public hearings are as follows: Date: 17 February (Friday) Time: 10H00 Venue: Moses Mabotha Community Hall – (Sekhukhune District Municipality)  Date: 18 February (Saturday) Time: 10H00 Venue: Makwarela Town Hall – (Vhembe District Municipality)  Date: 19 February (Sunday) Time: 10H00 Venue: Bela-Bela Recreational Hall (Waterberg District Municipality)  For media enquiries or interviews with the committee Chairperson, please contact: Name: Sakhile Mokoena Parliamentary Communication Services Cell: 081 705 2130 E-mail: smokoena@parliament.gov.za A joint committee of Parliament receives submissions on constitutional matters and has to review the Constitution at least once a year. Economic Freedom Fighters